*msmtp-1.4.5-r1 (28 Dec 2005)
*msmtp-1.4.5 (28 Dec 2005)

  28 Dec 2005; Tom Martin <slarti@gentoo.org> -msmtp-1.4.4-r1.ebuild,
  +msmtp-1.4.5.ebuild, +msmtp-1.4.5-r1.ebuild:
  Version bump, and purge old mailer.eclass-compatible version.

  02 Oct 2005; Aron Griffis <agriffis@gentoo.org> msmtp-1.4.2.ebuild:
  Mark 1.4.2 stable on ia64

  05 Sep 2005; Markus Rothe <corsair@gentoo.org> msmtp-1.4.2.ebuild:
  Stable on ppc64

  30 Aug 2005; Tom Martin <slarti@gentoo.org> msmtp-1.4.2.ebuild:
  Stable amd64, sparc, ia64.

*msmtp-1.4.4-r1 (21 Aug 2005)
*msmtp-1.4.4 (21 Aug 2005)

  21 Aug 2005; Tom Martin <slarti@gentoo.org> -msmtp-1.4.0-r1.ebuild,
  -msmtp-1.4.1-r1.ebuild, -msmtp-1.4.2-r1.ebuild, +msmtp-1.4.4.ebuild,
  +msmtp-1.4.4-r1.ebuild:
  Version bump to 1.4.4. Same deal with the mailer.eclass -r1. Purged older
  versions with mailer.eclass support: mailer-config remains package.masked.

*msmtp-1.4.2-r1 (08 Jul 2005)
*msmtp-1.4.2 (08 Jul 2005)

  08 Jul 2005; Tom Martin <slarti@gentoo.org> +msmtp-1.4.2.ebuild,
  +msmtp-1.4.2-r1.ebuild:
  Version bump, adds NLS support. Two variants, as ever, one for old-style
  mailwrapper and -r1 for new mailer.eclass support.

  05 Jul 2005; Tom Martin <slarti@gentoo.org> msmtp-1.4.1.ebuild,
  msmtp-1.4.1-r1.ebuild:
  Marked ~ia64.

  04 Jul 2005; Andrej Kacian <ticho@gentoo.org> msmtp-1.4.1-r1.ebuild:
  Better mailer-config compatibility.

*msmtp-1.4.1-r1 (27 May 2005)
*msmtp-1.4.1 (27 May 2005)

  27 May 2005; Tom Martin <slarti@gentoo.org> +msmtp-1.4.1.ebuild,
  +msmtp-1.4.1-r1.ebuild:
  Version bump. The -r1 is committed at the same time -- it's the
  package.masked variant with mailer.eclass support.

  08 May 2005; Tom Martin <slarti@gentoo.org> -msmtp-1.3.2-r1.ebuild:
  One more version purge.

